<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The dilemma if you are BlackRock Inc. is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A lot of your customers are concerned=
 about environmental, social and governance issues, believe that the climat=
e transition is coming, and want to make green or ESG investments with a fi=
rm that cares about ESG. Also many politicians around the world are concern=
ed about these issues and will apply regulatory pressure to make you more E=
SG.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some of your customers, and so=
me politicians, want the opposite: They want you to invest more in oil and =
coal companies, they want you to oppose corporate diversity efforts, they a=
re generally anti-ESG.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You are eno=
rmous and your job is to please everyone.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I sympathize, and I do not pretend to have the=
 answers; I don=E2=80=99t know how I would do this if I were them. My basic=
 instinct is =E2=80=9Cbe very quiet, offer=C2=A0regular funds and ESG funds=
 and load-up-on-coal funds, and hope nobody pays too much attention=E2=80=
=9D; I do think that=C2=A0<em>other </em>giant index and quasi-index manage=
rs do a better job of=C2=A0<em>not talking so much about ESG</em>, in ways =
that spare them a lot of negative attention from both sides.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is not BlackRock=E2=80=99s approach, thou=
gh. Like the other big managers, BlackRock offers regular funds and ESG fun=
ds, and it is a huge investor in oil and=C2=A0coal companies. But it also d=
oes (or, at least, did) a lot of <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/32118824.260407/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9u=
L2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDEtMTQvYmxhY2tyb2NrLWhhcy1ncmVlbi1wbGFucz9jbXBpZD1CQkQ=
wNzE4MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlci=
Z1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA3MTgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB26be1443" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">  noisy publicity</a> around its ESG efforts, and bal=
ances it out by <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32=
118824.260407/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtM=
DctMTcvYmxhY2tyb2NrLW5hbWVzLWFyYW1jby1jZW8tYW1pbi1uYXNzZXItdG8taXRzLWJvYXJk=
LW9mLWRpcmVjdG9ycz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNzE4MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWl=
sJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA3MTgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbm=
V5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1d0581d6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  sometimes doing=C2=
=A0noisy anti-ESG publicity</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BlackRock Inc. has named Saudi Aramco Chief Ex=
ecutive Officer Amin Nasser to its board, underscoring the asset manager=E2=
=80=99s commitment to the oil industry in the middle of a highly politicize=
d debate about its role in ESG investing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nasser has led the world=E2=80=99s biggest oil=
 producer since 2015, including overseeing its public listing, and provides=
 BlackRock with =E2=80=9Ca unique perspective=E2=80=9D on key issues facing=
 the company and its clients, CEO Larry Fink said Monday in an emailed stat=
ement.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BlackRock and Fink, 70, have been criticized b=
y both sides of the political divide over ESG investing after promoting the=
 strategy as a way to help the global economy respond to climate change. En=
vironmental advocates have slammed the firm for continuing to pile capital =
into the fossil fuel industry, while some Republicans have accused BlackRoc=
k of peddling a =E2=80=9Cwoke=E2=80=9D agenda that they say is at odds with=
 American capitalism.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Ca very cunning move,=E2=
=80=9D said Sasja Beslik, chief investment officer at NextGen ESG in Japan.=
</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is? Really? US Republican politicians are g=
onna be like =E2=80=9Coh, BlackRock is fine now, they have a Saudi oil exec=
utive on the board=E2=80=9D? Who is going to be happy with this precise com=
bination?=C2=A0I would just=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>write a lot of letters t=
o CEOs about how important climate change is, and also=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</=
em>put a Saudi oil executive on the board. The way to construct an investme=
nt-company board is not to have a bunch of climate activists and balance th=
em with a bunch of oil executives. It=E2=80=99s to have a bunch of apolitic=
al finance people and hope nobody ever bothers to find out who they are.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere in BlackRock <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32118824.260407/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL=
2NvbnRlbnQvM2YwZjI2YmYtY2IzMy00ZmQ0LWExZGQtNDEwNGNkMjk0YjE3P3JlZj10aGVkaWZm=
LmNv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB734997f9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> trying to please everyone<=
/a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BlackRock will give retail investors in its bi=
ggest exchange traded fund the chance to participate in proxy voting in 202=
4, as the $9.4tn asset manager moves to rebut Republican claims that it pur=
sues a =E2=80=9Cwoke agenda=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The world=E2=80=99s biggest money manager has =
joined fellow index fund providers State Street and Vanguard in experimenti=
ng with ways to involve ordinary investors in voting on shareholder proposa=
ls at a time when their collective influence on US companies has come under=
 fire from both left and right.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Investors in BlackRock=E2=80=99s iShares Core =
S&amp;P 500 ETF will be asked to choose among seven different general polic=
ies ranging from voting generally with management to prioritising Catholic =
values or environmental, social and governance factors. Investors can also =
tell BlackRock to continue voting their shares. Customers will not be able =
to cast specific votes on individual companies.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The idea is that BlackRock gives you a menu of=
 voting=C2=A0<em>policies</em>, and you choose one, and then BlackRock appl=
ies that policy to do the actual voting on the (hundreds and hundreds) of p=
roposals that the fund votes on. =E2=80=9CThe <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/32118824.260407/aHR0cHM6Ly9maW5hbmNlLnlhaG9vLmN=
vbS9uZXdzL2JsYWNrcm9jay1leHBhbmRzLXByb3h5LXZvdGluZy1yZXRhaWwtMjMzNzM2MDkwLm=
