 solve some of Twitter=E2=80=99s short-term problems. For one thing, he mig=
ht be able to invest money in hiring more engineers so he can fix the probl=
ems with Twitter=E2=80=99s technical infrastructure. That in turn could cha=
nge the overwhelmingly negative narrative about the company right now. Othe=
rwise, Twitter is stuck in a situation like that facing many money-losing s=
tartups, which don=E2=80=99t want to raise money at a lower valuation than =
their 2021 peak but can=E2=80=99t afford not to. Those startups will have t=
o eventually bite the bullet on valuation. The same applies to Musk=E2=80=
=99s Twitter.</p></blockquote>
